    "heading_text": "Shortcut",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/dependencies/classes-as-dependencies/#shortcut",
    "chunk_index": 0,
    "chunk_text": "Shortcut. But you see that we are having some code repetition here, writing CommonQueryParams twice: FastAPI provides a shortcut for these cases, in where the dependency is specifically a class that FastAPI will \"call\" to create an instance of the class itself. For those specific cases, you can do the following: Instead of writing: ...you write: You declare the dependency as the type of the parameter, and you use Depends() without any parameter, instead of having to write the full class again inside of Depends(CommonQueryParams) . The same example would then look like: ...and FastAPI will know what to do.",
